# ğŸ§ `unalias` Command (from manual)

### ğŸ“Œ Syntax

```bash
unalias [-a] name [name ...]
```

### ğŸ“Œ Options

* **`unalias name`** â†’ removes one alias.

  ```bash
  unalias ll
  ```
* **`unalias -a`** â†’ removes *all* aliases at once.

  ```bash
  unalias -a
  ```

### âŒ Example

```bash
alias hi='echo Hello'
hi          # prints "Hello"
unalias hi  # remove it
hi          # now says "command not found"
```

