# âš¡ Quick Reference (Cheat Sheet)

| Command                | Meaning               |
| ---------------------- | --------------------- |
| `alias`                | List all aliases      |
| `alias name='command'` | Create alias          |
| `alias name`           | Show alias definition |
| `unalias name`         | Remove single alias   |
| `unalias -a`           | Remove all aliases    |

---

âœ… So, **alias** doesnâ€™t really have flags like `-r`, but **unalias has `-a`** (all).
The `-r` option you heard about actually belongs to other commands (like `rm -r` or `rmdir -r`), not to alias.

